# Code Style & Naming

## Formatting (Prettier)
- 2-space indentation, semicolons, single quotes, trailing commas, `printWidth: 120`
- Run formatter: `pnpm -F <workspace> prettier -- <file>`

## Naming
- Components: `PascalCase`
- Variables, functions, methods: `camelCase`
- Workspace/package directories: `kebab-case`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## TypeScript
- Always use `import type { ... }` for type-only imports (`@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports`)
- Avoid `any`; if unavoidable, add `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` with a comment explaining why
- Prefer explicit return types on exported functions

## Module Boundaries
- Background service worker (`chrome-extension/src/background/`) is the only place that touches LLM/agent logic
- UI pages (`pages/`) communicate with the background via Chrome messaging only — no direct agent imports
- Shared logic belongs in `packages/`; never duplicate across workspaces

## Vite Path Aliases
- `chrome-extension/`: `@root`, `@src`, `@assets` (see `chrome-extension/vite.config.mts`)
- `pages/*`: `@src` (use `packages/vite-config`'s `withPageConfig`)
- Never use relative `../../` imports across workspace boundaries — use the alias or a package import

## Do Not Touch
- `dist/**`, `build/**`, `packages/i18n/lib/**` — generated, do not edit
- `turbo.json`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, root `tsconfig*` — require approval
